Rules:
- Make each scene a useful teaching visual, not a generic illustration.
- For each scene, first decide the teaching concept: what should become clearer visually than it is in audio alone.
- Choose on-slide text as labels, contrast markers, formula words, or a short takeaway. It must support the concept, not repeat the narration.
